div.div:
This sequence diagram displays the methods and messages used when a player wants to play a game. The case reported is a correct exchange of messages and does not show actions taken if a nack has to be sent. Furthermore is not shown in details the case in which the lobby is full and the game has to be created.
Important notes are about the method addToLobby and the participant "Client". The method used here represents all the four methods which call depends on the number of players chosen by the client. The Client is schematizedto represent either a cli or a gui
